%N A394602 Decimal expansion of the mean distance between two points selected independently at random within the interior of a rectangle with dimensions 1 X 2.
%C A394602 In general, the mean distance for a rectangle with dimensions a x b is ((a^2/b)*arccosh(r/a) + (b^2/a)*arccosh(r/b))/6 + (b^3/a^2 + a^3/b^2)/15 - (r/15)*(b^2/a^2 + a^2/b^2 - 3), where r = sqrt(a^2+b^2) (Czuber, 1884; Gosh,1951).
%D A394602 Luis A. Santaló, Integral Geometry and Geometric Probability, 2nd ed., Cambridge University Press, 2004, p. 49.
%H A394602 Emanuel Czuber, <a href="https://archive.org/details/geometwahrschein00czubrich/page/n215/mode/1up">Geometrische Wahrscheinlichkeiten und Mittelwerte</a>, Leipzig, B. G. Teubner, 1884, p. 204.
%H A394602 Brahim Gaboune, Gilbert Laporte and François Soumis, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/2583917">Expected Distances between Two Uniformly Distributed Random Points in Rectangles and Rectangular Parallelpipeds</a>, The Journal of the Operational Research Society, Vol. 44, No. 5 (1993), pp. 513-519.
%H A394602 Birendranath Ghosh, <a href="https://archive.org/details/dli.calcutta.11610/page/17/mode/1up">Random distances within a rectangle and between two rectangles</a>, Bulletin of Calcutta Mathematical Society, Vol. 43 (1951), pp. 17-24.
%H A394602 A. M. Mathai, P. Moschopoulos, and G. Pederzoli, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02844387">Random points associated with rectangles</a>,  Rendiconti del Circolo Matematico di Palermo, Vol. 48 (1999), pp. 163-190.
%H A394602 H. J. Oser, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/2028896">Problem 75-12, An Average Distance</a>, SIAM Review, Vol. 17, No. 3 (1975), p. 566; <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/2028652">Solution</a>, by J. D. Murchland and D. J. Daley, ibid., Vol. 18, No. 3 (1976), pp. 497-501. See p. 498.
%F A394602 Equals (33 - 5*sqrt(5) + 5*arcsinh(2)) + 40*log(phi))/60, where phi is the golden ratio (A001622).
%e A394602 0.804771841512987352172181198244731368253867443219228...
%t A394602 RealDigits[(33 - 5*Sqrt[5] + 5*ArcSinh[2] + 40*Log[GoldenRatio])/60, 10, 120][[1]]
%o A394602 (PARI) my(phi = quadgen(5)); (33 - 5*sqrt(5) + 5*asinh(2) + 40*log(phi))/60
